node.text: Lucia and Agustin of @proyectopasillodeco's home used to belong to Lucia's grandparents and looked nothing like it does today. The pair made the space much brighter by getting rid of the dark, old wallpaper, and then got to work transforming each room one DIY at a time. They did such a great job, it's no wonder they were crowned our 2021 Small/Cool contest winners! 👑

node.title: This 2021 Small/Cool Winner's Argentina Home Is Full of DIYs

node.text: Music teacher @kirstymarie23’s New York studio is remarkably functional and cozy despite the small size! Kirsten and her dad added a backsplash over the oven, painted and hung cabinets, built a loft, retiled the bathroom floor, added a sink to the basin of the toilet, as well as many other small fixes/additions here and there. “Together, we made it great, and it feels like a true New York Apartment,” she says.

node.text: Graphic designer and artist Laura Horstmann has filled every room of her rental with vibrant color, cool art, and loads of style. "It's like Lisa Frank meets Hot Topic with a sprinkling of theater kid, rhinestone cowboy, and disco daddy," @prozacefron describes. Check out the bold murals, wall of shoes, and so much more!

node.text:
This 135-year-old Seattle loft proves the power of a little paint and a lot of furniture rearranging. This isn’t the first time that we shared a look into Taylor’s stylish brick space, but today it’s a totally different space than it was then. “I have redone the entire kitchen, both bathrooms, and the overall design of the space including paint, lighting, fixtures, etc.,” explains @_atomicred. Tour the rest of this lovely brick loft at the link in our bio. 

(Image: @sarahzeutenhorst; Home: @_atomicred)

node.text: While there’s no way to make washing a mountain of baby laundry fun, there are little tricks that will make it bearable.
